claim.claim-text:
1. A method comprising:
automatically selecting, by a processing device, previous customers of a product using a plurality of customer records from previous product orders for the product;
concatenating, by the processing device, a plurality of enriched customer records for the previous customers based on adding customer demographic information to the plurality of customer records, wherein the customer demographic information comprises a plurality of variables;
creating, by the processing device, a product demographic profile for the product from the plurality of enriched customer records, the product demographic profile comprising automatically scored target demographics for the product based at least in part on a combination of the customer demographic information from the plurality of enriched customer records;
receiving media demographic profiles for a plurality of advertising media assets, the media demographic profiles being based on viewer demographic information;
calculating similarity measures between the product demographic profile for the product and the plurality of media demographic profiles for the plurality of advertising media assets; and
selecting an advertising media asset from the plurality of advertising media assets based on a calculated similarity measure between the product demographic profile for the product and a media demographic profile of the selected advertising media asset.

5. A method comprising:
automatically selecting, by a processing device, known customers of one or more previously advertised products advertised with a media asset using a first plurality of customer records for the one or more previously advertised products;
concatenating, by the processing device, a first plurality of enriched customer records for the known customers of the one or more previously advertised products based on adding customer demographic information to the first plurality of customer records, wherein the customer demographic information comprises a plurality of variables;
creating, by the processing device, a media asset demographic profile for the media asset from the first plurality of enriched customer records;
receiving product demographic profiles for a plurality of additional products to be advertised, wherein a product demographic profile for a particular product comprises automatically scored target demographics for the particular product based at least in part on a combination of customer demographic information from a second plurality of enriched customer records from previous product orders for the particular product, the product profiles for the plurality of additional products having been generated without user input of the target demographics;
calculating similarity measures between the product demographic profiles for the plurality of additional products and the media asset demographic profile; and
selecting one of the plurality of additional products to advertise with the media asset based on a similarity between the media asset demographic profile and the product demographic profile of the selected additional product.

11. A method comprising:
identifying, by a processing device, buyers of a product using a linking key embedded in an advertisement for the product associated with a television media asset, wherein the identified buyers are included in a plurality of buyer records;
creating, by the processing device, a plurality of enriched buyer records based on adding buyer demographic information to the plurality of buyer records, wherein the buyer demographic information comprises a plurality of variables;
creating, by the processing device, a media asset demographic profile from the enriched buyer records;
calculating a standardized score for at least some of the variables for the media asset; and
using the standardized scores to predict attributes of viewers for the television media asset.

14. A method of placing an advertisement for a product, the method comprising:
automatically selecting, by a processing device, a first set of known customers of the product using a plurality of customer records from previous product orders for the product;
concatenating, by the processing device, a first set of enriched customer records for the first set of known customers based on adding customer demographic information to the plurality of customer records, wherein the customer demographic information comprises a plurality of variables;
creating, by the processing device, a product demographic profile for the product from the first set of enriched customer records, the product demographic profile comprising automatically scored target demographics for the product based at least in part on a combination of the customer demographic information from the first set of enriched customer records;
automatically selecting a second set of known customers of one or more previously advertised products advertised with a plurality of media assets using a second plurality of customer records for the one or more previously advertised products;
concatenating a second set of enriched customer records for the second set of known customers for each of the plurality of media assets based on adding additional customer demographic information to the second plurality of customer records, wherein the additional customer demographic information comprises at least some of the plurality of variables;
creating a media asset demographic profile for each of the plurality of media assets from each of the second set of enriched customer records;
calculating a standardized discrepancy between the product demographic profile and each of the plurality of media asset demographic profiles; and
identifying one or more media assets from the plurality of media assets for placing the advertisement for the product based upon the calculated standardized discrepancies.

15. A system for profiling customers of a product, the system comprising:
at least one database configured to store demographic information; and
a processor, communicatively coupled to the at least one database, and configured to:
automatically select a set of known customers of a product using a set of customer records from previous product orders for the product;
concatenate a set of enriched customer records for the set of known customers based on adding customer demographic information from the at least one database to the set of customer records, wherein the customer demographic information comprises a plurality of variables;
create a product demographic profile for the product from the set of enriched customer records, the product demographic profile comprising automatically scored target demographics for the product based at least in part on a combination of the customer demographic information from the set of enriched customer records;
receive media demographic profiles for a plurality of advertising media assets, the media demographic profiles being based on viewer demographic information;
calculate similarity measures between the product demographic profile for the product and the plurality of media demographic profiles for the plurality of advertising media assets; and
select a advertising media asset from the plurality of advertising media assets based upon the calculated similarity between the product demographic profile and a media demographic profile of the selected advertising media asset.

17. A system for profiling a media asset, the system comprising:
at least one database configured to store demographic information; and
a processor, communicatively coupled to the at least one database, and configured to:
automatically select a first set of known customers of one or more previously advertised products advertised with a media asset using a first set of customer records for the one or more products;
concatenate a first set of enriched customer records for the first set of known customers of the one or more previously advertised products based on adding customer demographic information from the at least one database to the first set of customer records, wherein the customer demographic information comprises a plurality of variables;
create a media asset demographic profile for the media asset from the first set of enriched customer records;
receive product demographic profiles for a plurality of additional products to be advertised, wherein a product demographic profile for a particular product comprises automatically scored target demographics for the particular product based at least in part on a combination of customer demographic information from a second set of enriched customer records from previous product orders for the particular product, the product demographic profiles for the plurality of additional products having been generated without user input of the target demographics;
calculate similarity measures between the product demographic profiles for the plurality of additional products and the media asset demographic profile; and
select one of the plurality of additional products to advertise with the media asset based on a similarity between the media asset demographic profile and the product demographic profile of the selected additional product.
